reviews.text: We went with out three kids (3, 6, and 7). They have a nice series of children's exhibits, and there is a great interactive section for kids as well. We all liked the glasswork and silver work. There was a large section of art from local children artists (K-12) that our kids enjoyed and seemed to appreciate more than the other galleries. The museum building itself is located next to a park with a large fish pond and walking paths that we also enjoyed.

We mostly patronize the Academy for art classes. My kids have enjoyed and learned a lot from attending classes at the museum. The offerings are varied, unique, and touch on multiple mediums. We just finished up Cartooning & Ceramics and both kids had great experiences. We've also been pleased with the weeklong summer programs, and don't miss the museum gift shop! Great unique and some locally made gifts for all ages.

Really nice museum with very interesting collections. I really.like how the galleries are laid out. It's a small.museum, more of a gallery but you could spend a whole morning or afternoon here. It's a great facility and I was really happy with the variety in the galleries.

Had a wonderful evening with my mom and dad during the Alphonse Mucha preview reception. It was my first time being part of an event at the Huntsville Museum of Art. I plan on going to every event I can from here on out.
A wonderful place to visit at all times.I also am gifted to work here.I have learn about the many talents of Art .

Loved the kid area, they have so many kitchen items. There's a cash register with play money. They have a lot of dress up clothes for boys and girls. Toy's for smaller kids. The had a train and a truck to play in and climb on. We didn't even have time to tour the rest of the place, we spent so much time in the kid room.

We took our train loving son here and were treated to a lovely tour by a gentleman who worked there. He told us some interesting history of Huntsville. We were able to wander the grounds for a while. To my sons delight we even saw a modern freight train go by!

Wonderful stories! The staff was so helpful. We found it on accident so 8t was a very pleasant surprise adventure. They were very accommodating too since we strived just a little after the tour started.
This is a really interesting fun place. I was here for an event an it was a great experience. It's perfect for kids.

Interesting pieces of railway history. The preserved and restored railway machines are cool, but the depot itself and where people used to board the trains is my favorite. It's sort of like looking back in time.

Great place to go and take the kids. They have really good historical buildings. I actually worked then and replaced the siding recectly. It already looked really good, and now looks much better. They also have tours you can take. They show you how everything was done back in the 1800s. Also having live animals to help preserve how people lived a few hundred years ago. Really good place and neat to visit.

This place is gorgeous! It is the perfect wedding/reception location in Huntsville. However, there are no hotels there and you would need to bus your guests from the wedding to the reception and/or the hotel.
In the alternative, you can have an alcohol free wedding.
I went here with my son's class as a field trip and absolutely loved the hike and the whole outdoor experience.. I will definitely be returning to enjoy with family and friends..
Beautiful view. Just make sure you get there before they close. If you don't, it's no big deal. You'll just have to go up a steep hill from the entrance.
Great experience.  Learning about the natural beauty of what Huntsville has to offer Alabama.

We love this store so much. It's an old hardware store that got turn into a novelty shop. It still has all the old things from the hardware store and it's just charming. The women who work there are so kind and just love the store.

A great staff with people always concerned with the customers welfare and concerns. The store is governed by a board which is always reviewing ways to make it better. Profits are not top priority at this store and the staff members are indeed happy to be working there with the ability to help and deal with the public. The store gets high praise in thorough thought on what to stock that visitors would desire that is special to represent a special town that they all are tremendously proud of. They want a customer to leave with an item that they can say, this is something special and, I will always remember Harrison Brothers of Huntsville, Alabama.
Love going to this store. Brings back memories from my childhood. Always find something new and interesting.

I came here with a bunch of my family on a family history tour.  My daughter and I enjoyed looking around at all the neat things and purchased a bag of marbles and several other things.  Knowing that ancestors shopped in that same store generations ago was really cool!
Love Harrison Brothers!  All kinds of neat items for sale.  Totally run by very sweet volunteers

Sparking young minds into the wonderful world of science!
Sci-Quest makes science fun for people young and old, with interactive experiments and great exhibits. The friendly staff are always there to help.
When I was young, I always loved to see what was new every visit. From growing DNA and making it visible to dissecting snakes.  Sci-Quest brings it all!

While not all together bad, a good amount of the exhibits did not function either all together or were partially broke. From the looks this has been a long standing problem. For the price their asking I wouldn't go again.
Very good overall. Some broken exhibits but young kids love it! Hopefully it's better when they move from Calhoun community college.
Great idea but horrible execution. Most of the exhibits are not working or missing parts. My children enjoyed it but pretty sure they could of had as much fun playing at mcdonalds for free.
It is easy to see why this place closed. There really wasn't a lot there for the price. A lot of things were broken too.

I attended a free event here with my girlfriend. It was really neat getting to poke around a historic Huntsville home! I really enjoyed it, and would recommend it to anyone who appreciates historic homes/architecture.

Has an expanded exhibit for the Alabama Bicentennial. From February 1-March 7 2019. The home, furnishings, paintings, etc. give a good sense of life before and after the Civil War. Great way to learn more about local Huntsville area history. Guides knowledgeable and helpful.
Officiated a wedding here back on Dec 15 and the house was beautiful. Perfect for a picturesque wedding or reception. Very intimate.
Beautiful home with rich history. We had a birthday tea here. Staff very accommodating and helpful!

My Granddaughter had her wedding held there. It is a small place with pre-civil war features about it and has been held as so but with modern emenities.It was a hot evening 90°F. However it was comfortable under the huge pecan tree's there.nice for a wedding.

Great trails, disc golf course, camping areas and more. There are adorable rustic cabins available as well as separate camping areas for RVs and tent campers. Hiking trails are easily accessible from the overnight areas, buildings and grounds are well-maintained. Wonderful variety of landscapes to enjoy due to the mountain setting, yet it’s just a few minutes to drive into town. This is a great park and a huge part of the reason I moved to Huntsville. :)

Oh my! such a beautiful park! Get a spot overlooking the town below! Breath taking at night! Make sure to read email with the easiest way up the mountain.  Google takes you up a lot of switch backs. If you are pulling an RV like us it was white knuckle. READ EMAIL PRIOR to going up the mountain. The folks were so helpful. Restroom clean. Oh and don't miss the Japanese garden outside of the camp store. Its initial appearance is deceiving, a nice surprise.
Beautiful park, Gorgeous landscape. Great for a date night or just to take the kids to pass the time. Machine dispensers to feed the ducks and fish, lit up at night. Breath taking scenery.

Gorgeous! Monte Sano is beautiful and provides a variety of hiking trails, gardens, playgrounds, cabins, and a large lodge. There also many picnic areas. You can tell the park is well-kept, even though there’s been some work going on with uprooted trees (maybe from the recent floods?) The trails were clear and well marked and there was no trash. There is plenty of parking, and the entrance fees are $5 per person. It’s a pet-friendly area as well and looks like a great place to bring your furry friends. The entrance attendant was friendly and let us know the park closes at sundown - gates are locked at that point. I plan to return soon for a great day of picnicking and hiking!

Enjoyed our stay in a cabin here. I would like to go again! Great place for walking, hiking, bicycles, and walking your dog on a leash. Nice mini kitchens with all the necessary dishes, cutlery, pots, pans and utensils provided. Good refrigerator, electric stove and oven are provided for your use. Cable TV. Air-conditioning and a fireplace.  Very clean shower and small vanity sink. Our rustic and cozy cabin had 2 comfortable twin beds as it was my elderly mother and myself staying about 4 or 5 nights. Your bed linens are furnished.  If you have a physical handycap, you need to discuss that with the reservation staff when you call to make reservations. Most of the cabins are difficult to get into from the asphalt roads; the pathway from where your car is parked to the door of the porch is rather uneven and is rough going for use of a walker of any kind, but not impossible. If you use a wheelchair, this is not the place for you. There are no sidewalks (as of summer of 2017). Fortunately, my mother was in very good condition for her age (84) and wasn't using any cane or walker at all.  Book your stay 4 to 6 months in advance.  The staff are very pleasant, efficient and helpful; they will happily answer all of your questions! A great place for enjoying nature, relaxing and unwinding, and for daily exercise. And it is quiet!

Awesome place to go with your family we make plans to go every year for the Earth Day festivities and are very impressed with the wonderful facilities in this beautiful area. Thank you to the Hays family for allowing it to be used for so many wonderful events and we plan on visiting much more this year to have some family picnics and hiking or fishing. There are lots of different things for all ages.

Absolutely lovely and perfect for all ages! The playground is without a doubt the best one around here, and perhaps in the city (I haven't seen every single one, so I can't say definitively 😊). It is set in a ton of mature trees so there is plenty of shade which really helps when it's warm/hot out. There are bathrooms to the side of the playground and they're in good condition. There are picnic tables perfect for snacks, any meal, or just sitting down while the kids run themselves straight into nap time or bed time.

The equipment itself is perfect. Every thing is constructed of wood and feels so natural in the setting in the woods. There are plenty of adventures to be had for all ages. My 3&5 yo love it, and my 12 yo enjoys going as well. Lots to climb on, swing on, explore, and really let their imaginations go wild.

If you haven't been here, pack up and go today, you will be so glad you did!
Had a great time on the playground with my nephew.  He especially loved the climbing pieces and the music area.  A beautiful day to walk around the pond.

One of the best local places for kids. Our family could spend the whole day there. Best of all, it's free!  They have picnic tables, a huge wood playground, and fishing. If you need some alone time, there are plenty of running and hiking trails. During the week it's pretty deserted. Except the occasional field trip day. On the

Kids love the playground area up front, and the paved path that crosses the river is nice. Haven't been in a while, but you need to plan accordingly if there has been a lot of rain as the path across the river floods over. If the river is really high, I'd keep to the main park side of the river.

Great place to get quick Mexican. There isn't a lot of seating so if you have a larger group make sure you are prepared to sit outside. They have a decent selection and options for vegans/vegetarians.
You get lots of good food at a decent price, and the decor matches the vibe the place gives off. What's not to love?

This place is 2 steps above Taco Bell. Food is nothing to write home about. I've only had the green sauce  bean burrito (the sause is sub par) and the nachos. 
The friendly staff is what makes this place stand out  (and the pic of ice cube on the ice machine).
Love this place. Brings back part of my childhood. Sucks that the surrounding area is rough.

Loved the salsa with fresh green onions and garlic.  I order off the dinner menu and got the enchilada, taco, with rice and beans; all were tasty. Taco shell was crunchy and, for lack of a better word, flaky.... was good.

We have been here numerous times and love it every time! Staff is wicked, and probably the best food in town, I had a steak which I typically do not get at a restaurant because I am usually disappointed, not at brewbakers! Probably the best steak I have ever eaten!

Great spot. Dined on the special which was a crab pasta dish and also the seared Pork tenderloin. Staff was attentive and friendly. Food was remarkably splendid in taste. The pork was cooked perfectly. A definite hit and will be back.

Great restaurant in the downtown of Fredericton. They have delicious food, a good selection of alcoholic beverages and a great ambiance. I would strongly recommend this place for dates, get togethers or professional outings.
Very beautiful pub. A great place to just have a very good meal and relax. Would highly recommend it.
Great food great service. Celebrated birthday and did not regret choosing BrewBakers.
I can't believe Bison's is closing! They have always had amazing wings and good drink specials. Trivia nights always brought a good crowd. Guess I'll have to find another wing place in Madison!
The food is amazing! The staff is super friendly.  Nice overall atmosphere.

Bison's is one of most delicious well kept secrets around. The wings whether traditional or boneless are top notch.  The hot sauce seems to be based on Frank's Red Hot.  That always makes for the best wings. The fries are great. They are long, thin, and wide.  A tad crunchy on the outside while soft inside.  They have some really good lunch specials.  Tuesdays has great deals on traditional and boneless chicken wings.  The bar is a smoking section and there's a separate dining room that's non smoking.  Nice patio dining areas for warmer weather.  The sweet tea is always very good and sweet.  Hardly ever seems too busy at dinner.  Lunch can be pretty packed sometimes.  They seem to keep staff low due to lesser amounts of customers so it can be a little slow on the service side if busy.  That said the servers always work hard and do a great job!
Food was okay and it is one of the only places that I know that allows smoking in their bar area
Great food. Great service. Relaxed atmosphere. Reasonable prices. Good selection of meals. We've added it as a regular place to dine.

I may be biased on my review here because I honestly love their food. My favorite meal is the spicy Cajun chicken pasta bowl. There aren't many restaurants that actually serve spicy food when the title says "spicy". This one really is spicy. They have other spicy dishes and they mark them on level of spicynes so you know ahead of time. If you take kids they tend to bring their meal out first which I like. You choose where to sit they have booth like areas as well as tables. They bring your food to you. For a family of 5 all of which ordered food & drinks we spend around $60 not bad. Kids plates are reasonably big. We always have left overs. They have chicken tenders, cheese pizza, spaghetti and Mac and cheese for kids menu. Nice relaxed place to go to.

Don't let the name fool you- this place has noodle free menu items too! My kids get noodles and I can get a low carb dish, so we all enjoy this place.  Plus, they have several types of unsweetened teas to choose from,  which I love.

I'm wondering if some of these 5-star reviews are fake. This is mediocre microwave food at best. Watery sauce and slimy pasta ready so quickly there's no way it's made fresh to my order. Well, at least it wasn't served on paper plates and it was quick.
Clean, friendly staff, and fast service. Still think the prices are a bit high for the food, but not a bad location.
This place is absolutely AWESOME. They have something that appeals to everyone. Food is served fresh, fast and hot. I wish they had one of these in Chattanooga, TN

I love this place we ordered their spring rolls definitely get the full appetizer. One is not enough. I could have eaten all eight by myself. They were definitely house made. Our waitress Sue actually helps make them. The staff spends hours making them. They fry them to order. My entree was amazing next time I'll get it at 3 stars of heat. My date got a curry dish and I liked it more than my noodle dish. For kids I would suggest the chicken appetizer with some rice and more spring rolls. The wait staff was amazing. Definitely will be going back and sending all of my friends and family.

It's located in the cozy popular 5 Points neighborhood which means parking is a bit limited. I ordered a cashew nut stirfry which was quite flavorful and Thai hot as I had hoped. 😊However, I ordered tofu as my protein with extra broccoli and the portions were disappointingly small even for a lunch menu. But I'm game to go again and check out the dinner menu and evening ambiance.
Delicious food, friendly and helpful service, great prices. The soups were excellent. I had spicy fried rice and thoroughly enjoyed it.
I've been going there since 1999. Same menu, same flavor, same location. Great place to try traditional Thai cuisine.

Ordered 2 pots of coconut soup, one w tofu and one w extra shrimp. The soup wasntwgood. It didn't have coconut taste. Tofu was tough, almost hard .The one w shrimp, had 6 med ones, also looks like broth from beef not coconut at all .Spri Sp rolls are smaller than before and hollow. Big waste of money. Since they changed hands, I guess they changed recipes. I don't like the change.

Seemed like a nice establishment on our first visit. Waited for someone to seat us then l had to tell a gentleman behind the counter we are dining in. He politely waved his hand to a booth so we seated ourselves. We also waited 15 more minutes while staff walked pass us and two other staff members were rolling silverware at a table next to us. There was one couple on our side of the dining area maybe a few more on the other side. My wife and daughter just left and ate next door at the Sun Cafe which was very good. I may go back,but was very disappointed.

The food here was delicious! It was served quickly and hot, and was priced reasonably. The serving size was massive and I ate what I had left over for lunch the following day. I would definitely recommend Viet Huong!
This place is bustling during the weekday lunch times but you still get in fast.  The service was very good.  I highly recommend the chicken clay pot meal.  It was delicious!

I'm just a girl from Florence, AL looking for pho wherever I can find it, and Viet Huong delivered! The staff were super nice and the service was super fast. Everything was delicious, and if I could I'd live in their kitchen for the rest of my life.

This will ALWAYS be a favorite throughout my friends and family! Come for the pho, Thai tea, and clay pots .....truly HEAVEN and I'm so glad they were able to expand into the other side of the restaurant. They are not a little secret hole in the wall anymore, but I'm okay with sharing 😁💗

Seems like family & they honor guest during happy times & sad times. They are uniquely comfortable with multiple atmospheres to choose from. They have a live concert area, a quiet cozy area, an outdoor area & a party all night area. Music surrounds all areas & it has a quiet music area for conversation. Small children are appropriate until around 8ish.
Always a pleasure to be served by the wonderful staff at the Furniture Factory. They go out of there way to welcome and serve you! Great food.

Great place to just hang out. DJ played some rockin tunes. Wait staff very engaging and customer focused. Good people there from all walks of life. Has an area in the back to enjoy a nice cigar. Very reasonable prices.

The atmosphere here is really what's to offer.  The food is ok, but will take a long time, and will leave you with serious heartburn if you're not careful. Much better to visit when the back patio is going.
Really great place a little different when you walk out back from in side, wait staff was great very friendly people as well

Sunday lunch was great! There was a nice cross breeze, the food was good, our server was great, and the live music was just the right volume and song choice. The kids loved the free dessert with their meal. We will be back!

The food was okay...the service, not so much. I appreciate "in the weeds" but that wasn't the case. Everything took forever. Drinks were left unfilled...and even undelivered. Getting our check was like pulling teeth. This was our second visit with the same experience, probably won't return for a third visit.

Husband and I came at sat at the bar last Monday.  Although we were disappointed they didn't have any grouper, we left very happy after sharing a big wing basket and a reuben sandwich!  The shrimp appetizer was also amazing!  Everything was such a good value for the the price we paid!  We definitely will be back!

HIGHLY DISAPPOINTED... I'm shocked they still have the nerve to call this A BEAUREGARD'S! DOUG WOULD BE SO DISAPPOINTED! Service was good, but limited since we got food to go. We got wing meals with fried okra, and fries loaned for side items with fried green tomatoes appetizer, and out bill was $40. That's kinda pricey to me, although I would not have minded so much if the food was worth it! I don't know if they change the original recipes for a cheaper vendor or what their thought process was either way they have failed epically bad! We used to love the mild teriyaki boneless wings, not anymore. The quality and taste is horrible, overpriced, and I will not be returning there for that experience ever again!

It's a shame the food can't be as great as the service!
Delicious food; friendly service. Affordable lunch prices. Definitely a local gem.

I asked them to make my sandwich a little different but I guess they decided that I was just going to have it their way. I don't appreciate that especially when they charge me extra for different cheese and then didn't give it to me I won't be back!!! The cashier that rang me up was really nice though that's the only reason why I'm giving him two stars.

My family and I stopped in for lunch on Saturday. They were hosting a birthday party and were quite busy. Nonetheless, our service was quick and the food was great! The manager, Kirsten, and his staff, made sure everyone was taken care of. The food was great, even the kid's menu items were tasty. 
All in all, this was a great place for comfort foods, helpful staff, and very reasonable prices! And one more thing: the carrot cake is delicious and HUGE!

**Update 3: Well no change. As March 2019 the lemonade machine is broken, no explanation and the service has been sustained to the same lackluster level. I would recommend you to pick another place. This one will never turn around for the better.

**Update 2: 3 months later. One thing has improved the staff is the same, but with that it includes same old problems.  The staff at the cashier still very rude, unattentive, lack the enthusiasm that makes me wonder, why I came back. My response the wife really enjoyed the food, but with no lemonade and the same bad service for me is an easy pass. Still 2yrs since the first time and a complete debacle on service management and lack of improvement. Not my first choice. Yes demotion to 2 stars, why no improvement over the service, food or even the environment. 

**Update: 1 month later. Staff changed, menus changed and the service still as bad as before. Waited easily 40min only 3 tables served and no rush. So far they are keeping up the bad service over and over. 

Service on decline. I have been at the place several times and with the management changes, I have seen how the service has taken a wrong turn. The place it is in a great location, but the staff keeps changing every other month. If there’s that much change it seems that the management is not able to keep their staff, so they are constantly figuring out how to in put your order. The last time the place was empty and the staff (all males) were pretty much more competing against each other to pick up a girl outside of the store. They pass each other comments and signals (clerk, 2 at the kitchen and one around the tables). I am a guy and I get it, but if you have to ask me 3 times about the same order and is just me ordering with no line. Please take the order and then move on. This place was one a weekly thing, but due to things like that, forgetting orders, ignoring customers or not having lemonades well is now more a one in a-few. The food is good, not great but good. If you want to change your routine it won’t be bad if you know what to expect at the location. Avoid weekdays or Saturdays at lunchtime it is near impossible to order, due to being very crowded.
Plenty of selections and food. Nice atmosphere and good service. A well established public place.

My wife and I decided to stop by for our first time and the staff was very welcoming and friendly. The sandwich and cheddar soup we both had was delicious! I would definitely be back and recommend to anyone.

I would HIGHLY recommend this place! The food is amazing, the service is excellent, and it has a nice atmosphere. It also has its own dedicated parking, which was a great bonus. I had the lamb and also added shrimp. I can easily say that was the best lamb I’ve had in ages! It was juicy tender and full of flavour. The bruschetta was also top notch. There isn’t a single thing I would change. I only wish I had heard of this place sooner. Can’t wait to go back!

This is the best place I have ever been to I got definitely recommened to other people because the food quality is amazing the staff are nice and i would defenitly recomened  if you have lot of money but if you dont want to pay 300$ then go to edo or somewhere cheaper. because my whole meal was 1200trillion dolaars including the tip of 99%. i love this place i have gone there lot and love the service the waiters are good looking and thats what i like:)

One of my favorite places in the city for Authentic Italian food.   The owner Michael is an extraordinary host that makes every guest feel like at home with his charming personality and outstanding service.   It's a must go to place for a romantic night or even a business meeting. The ambiance is great for any occasion.  Hands down the best risotto in calgary  and one of the few resturants that has parking aswell so next time you are in Kensington drop by for a light lunch or a relaxing authentic Italian dinner experience at a price everyone can afford.  A must try restaurant in Calgary.
I got a pile of GREY  slop served in pools of grease, GREASE GREASE GREASE. Only good if you are rich, and snobby.

Michele is a wonderful host and we eat there regularly.  Large parties, small parties, business lunch/ dinner or an intimiate night out Osteria caters to everyone.  Great food Great service Great atmosphere.

This place is great.  They have (what I would imagine is) authentic Thai food.  The food can be made at any spice level.  The coconut curry is amazing.  The location is fantastic, and they have a patio.  Their drinks are inexpensive.  The staff is always nice and welcoming, and I've never had an issue.  Would go again.

This is one of my favorite lunch spots. It is a quiet enough where you can actually have a conversation without yelling. I absolutely love the food, and if you want the spice turned up a bit they are happy to accommodate.  The lunch is always served in a timely manner and delicious.

“The secret of success in life is to eat what you like and let the food fight it out inside.” -Mark Twain

What a pleasant place to eat at!  Providence is a great area in its own right, but this Thai based restaurant is serious in their craft.  From the spring roles to the curries this spot has you covered if you are craving something spicy or sweet then this place can’t be beat (sorry for the rhyme), but in all seriousness take your spouse, a date, or even a friend out and you won’t regret the evening!  

Tip: If you are familiar with the cuisine and you know you want something not on the menu, if you can explain it or show a picture they will take care of you!

Nice comforting atmosphere. The food was amazing and the staff was great. We were a party of 8 with 4 children. We had more than enough room for our party. The staff was wonderful with our children. They had plenty of fun activities to keep them busy. A children's menu is available which I didn't see on the website. My finicky eaters (kids and adult) cleaned their plates there. We will definitely be returning often.

Located in the Providence community this place has consistently served up some of the most flavorful traditional Thai meals. The service is great sometimes seemingly a bit overwhelmed but always kind. Only thing I don't love is the water...it really has a super tap water taste🤷🏾‍♂️

What a fun place to go with a family that is really hungry and ready for some entertainment. This dining experience was entertaining from the start. Immediately as you get to the restaurant outside you have beautiful Japanese garden with some gorgeous prize-winning goldfishes. They kids had so much fun looking at them swimming and everything.  After all of that excitement we were able to be seated at a Japanese Hibachi Table with another family and kids so my children had a lot of fun interacting with everyone else around the table. As the chef came in he quickly started his show and it was fun interactive and very energetic. There was so much food!!!! Your portions are very large so make sure you come hungry. the typical Hibachi chicken dinner included rice vegetables and before that you get to have soup and salad. The only reason I took a star of was that the food was not as flavorful or authentic as I am used to but for being Japanese attraction chain spot it was sort of expected to be a little Bland however it was perfect for kiddos taste buds.

The food is surprisingly better than one might think. The salad that comes out with the soup prior to the meal is delicious I really like the dressing here. I did not care for the sushi as it did not seem as fresh as some places. The steak and chicken combo I ordered was well-cooked and affordable.

We arrived around 5:30, no one else in the dining area except for a group that was finishing up. We waited 15-20min before getting our drinks. A party of 16 arrived after we got our drinks. We had already ordered when another group joined our table. We still had not received our salads or soup an HOUR after being seated, but the party’s food was being cooked and served. Poor management. We were told that the party arrived before us, when they actually MOVED us from the table the party was sitting at to serve us quicker. The manager that I spoke with said “they knew what they wanted to eat, they had a list” I DON’T CARE if they had a list, we had ordered our food BEFORE the party placed their order. Waiting an hour and not receiving soups and salads is unacceptable in my book.

This place has always been pretty good. However the service has really gone down hill. No refills for the entire meal. Wrong food served. Appetizers brought after meal. Very small portions. Time to search for new place to eat.

Yes yes!! Best sushi presentation in Tennessee. Chef Boy knows how to make a birthday special. I told him to surprise me and yes I was surprised with a great sushi dinner.. will always be my go to place for sushi!!

When we first got there the lady ask how many we had, I told her six she ask us to wait till everybody was there to be seated. That was completely fine. Once seated we got drinks in and I ask for ranch on my salad and the waiter pops back with “ we only have house dressing” which is fine,but she was such a jerk about it. our hibachi chef was awesome! He did a great job, then we get our tickets... and give our cards and cash. She comes back AFTER taking our cards and had given herself a 5 dollar and something tip on everybody’s ticket. I have never had a Gratuity charge on hibachi! The fact that she waited to put it on there after she took our cards is just plain out wrong! Needless to say I won’t be going back because of her! She was snippy and rude  the whole time and we had to wait through half the meal for refills! The food was great and they the only reason I gave 2  stars but other than that the waitress ruined the experience for us!

Lobster tastes like it was seasoned in fingernail polish remover and it was crunchy like they left pieces from the shell on it. The “show” was lame. No onion train or trying to catch the shrimp in your mouth. The older waitress was a little snappy. Over all food was not to any standard. They were very fast though
It took a while to get seated. But once we did the food was great. I loved the soup and salad. And it's always fun to watch them cook in front of you.
It's okay....the chef we had didn't really "preform" much at all. The food wasn't anything to brag about, but it was okay. I will say our waitress along with the other staff was very nice.

Sushi is always worth the price.  Food very good, good presentation.  Staff always helpful and courteous.  Have never had a bad experience at Shogun.  This location has been around for at least 30yrs....there's probably a good reason!

Lovely night to spend with family and friends.  The side dishes were prepared to perfection--especially the sweet potatoes.  Biggest concern---my steak was way over cooked.  Ordered it medium rare....warm red center and it came out well done.  Not even a sign of pink.  This shouldn't happen at a top notch steak house.
Wait staff was awesome and food was superb. It’s tradition for us to find a Ruth Chris where ever we travel too. This one did not disappoint! Wonderful experience.

Totally overrated.  Ate here last night with a group of ten. Had the petite filet.  Said to the waiter that I wanted it cooked medium rare plus and then said maybe it should be medium.  He told me that it cooks very fast and I should order it medium rare.  I said okay and chose to have it cooked without butter.  I like to taste the meat.  You can put butter on feathers and it will taste great.  I guess that when they cook it and add the butter it makes the meat taste better than it really is.  So out comes our dinner and my steak is RARE and not even close to medium rare.   I ate a few bites because I was really hungry and I noticed it had a lot of pepper on it.  I finally flagged down our waiter and showed him the steak.  He agreed that it was rare and offered to bring me a hot plate, whatever good that would do, or take it back and cook it some more, which would probably dry the steak.  Since most of our party was well along in the meal, I opted to finish my steak, which by the way was not that good.  Maybe I should have had the butter.  I have had better meat from Costco prime steaks.  What a waste of money!

Consistency fantastic, the food is always delicious and the steak us done to perfection. 
We shared a large rib eye steak, medium rare, a mouth watering experience. The salads were fantastic as well- my wife enjoyed the Wedge and I loved the arugula salad.
The service is always top notch,  and our waiter Alex was attentive, friendly and made it a very pleasant evening. The martinis were great, and the cheesecake dessert with the salted caramel was devine. Obviously we will back!

Dined with family and friends and was not disappointed. The choice of steak and extensive side dishes was excellent. All our steaks were cooked as ordered and would recommend this restaurant to steak lovers visiting Waikiki. A little on the pricey side for a steak house but well worth it.

This was my first time here. It won't be the last. My standard order the first time at any Thai restaurant is the Chicken Pad Thai. If the Pad Thai is really good, I know it's a good restaurant.  This one has a wonderful Chicken and Shrimp Pad Thai on their lunch menu. The portion size was generous.  I also had the Thai tea, which was delicious. Unlike other Thai teas I have had, it was not too sweet. Definitely recommend this place!
It's always an awesome experience! at least for me and my wife. My favorite, eggplant spicy noodles.
Among many things squid rings were my most favorite.. Amazing place, nice staff... the best
This is one of my favorites. They food is always good. The barbecue chicken is awesome. I love the wedding cake martini. Great place to go for days night or out with friends.

I could live here.  I absolutely love this place.  The shrimp curry is fantastic and they are always accommodating when I ask for no green peppers and green beans.  Everything is so good here.  If you like Thai food - this should be your go to spot!
